			<div class="content" id="post-content-1994491">
									

<p>I would have liked this proposal, too. Definitely not the best, but not bad enough to warrant archival&#8230;until the point at the end about adding the drugs into the water supply.</p>
<p>I'm not going to pretend I have a lot of expertise in this area, but I'd say there's no way this would work. It's doubtful everyone at the site would eat and drink the exact same amount, so there's no telling how well it's going to work on any given person. Not to mention everyone has their own unique reaction to a drug. What if someone has a bad reaction? What if someone's on a med that has a bad reaction with prozac/paroxetine? The effects could be mind-altering (really bad for someone working with anomalous items) or fatal. Not to mention paroxetine has a good chance of giving someone withdrawls when they go off it.</p>
<p>So, no vote for me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
